<subSubSection pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="57.[151,1436,474,715]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1423852980" country="Madagascar" location="southern Arabia" municipality="Comoro Islands" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" specimenCount="1">
WL: 
<quantity box="[259,334,511,535]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" unit="mm" value="17.0">17mm</quantity>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[345,463,510,535]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pelopidas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mathias">
<emphasis box="[345,463,510,535]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">P. mathias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a ubiquitous pan-African skipper, present throughout sub-Saharan Africa, 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:A50287F3FFD4FFDAFF0EFE5CFC6EFD6D:2874603EFFD4FFDAFAA5FE78FF03FD9D" country="Madagascar" municipality="Comoro Islands" name="southern Arabia" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">southern Arabia</location>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[243,378,546,571]" name="Madagascar" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[438,622,546,571]" name="Comoros" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<collectingMunicipality box="[438,622,546,571]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Comoro Islands</collectingMunicipality>
</collectingCountry>
</materialsCitation>
. 
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1423852979" country="India" location="Oriental Region" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Oriental Region">
It extends to the 
<collectingRegion box="[830,1012,546,571]" country="Morocco" name="Oriental" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<collectingRegion box="[830,922,546,571]" country="Republic of the Congo" name="Orientale" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Oriental</collectingRegion>
Region
</collectingRegion>
(it was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[1289,1348,546,571]" name="India" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">India</collectingCountry>
) and to New 
<collectingCountry box="[211,296,582,607]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Guinea</collectingCountry>
. The caterpillars are polyphagous and feed on a variety of 
<taxonomicName box="[951,1047,583,606]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
